text:
East 159th Street, south side, from Walton Ave. to Grand Concourse, showing the Bronx Headquarters of the Boy Scouts of America. The building was later razed and on its site erected the Bronx County Court House. The street, at this point, was also obliterated, when the court house was put up extending from East 158 to 161st Streets.

May 16, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

Grand Concourse (Mott Ave.), at the S.E. corner of East 158th Street, showing the Fleischmann Laboratories. The view is southeastward across East 158th Street.

May 16, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Bronx: Grand Concourse - 158th Street (East)

text:
Grand Concourse (left), west side, south from East 161st to East 158th Street, showing the Bronx County Court House. On the right is the East 161st street side of the court house, extending west to Walton Ave. Also shown is the north end of Franz Sigel Park at East 158th Street. 1933.

Wurtz Brothers.
title: Bronx: Grand Concourse - 158th Street (East)

text:
Grand Concourse, west side, from East 161st to E. 158th Streets, showing the new Bronx County Court House, which replaced the old one at Third and Brook Avenues. Views 1 and 2 are south from E. 162nd Street; view 3 is north from E. 157th Street.

Views 1,2: July 7, 1936
View 3: June 9, 1940

P. L. Sperr
